author: enridaga
msg: We change how the default rule store file location is set, giving a string result from a URI instance instead of a FS location. This attribute, passed as string, is then used to create the physical IRI of the ontology. On windows platforms this caused the problems described in STANBOL-255.

author: hwright
msg: When commiting, don't bother attempting to write packed revprops.  A new
revision should never be packed (at least not before it's written).
(commit_body): Don't both checking to see if we should we writing to the
packed revprop db.  Assert that this rev doesn't have packed revprops.
